# Documentation Site

Docusaurus 3 site. Content pages live in `docs/docs/` — not the `docs/` workspace root.

## When to update

Any change to `action.yml` inputs, defaults, or user-facing behavior must update the matching page under `docs/docs/`.

Key pages:
- `docs/docs/reference/configuration.md` — input reference
- `docs/docs/reference/architecture.md` — pipeline and modules
- `docs/docs/development.md` — dev setup

## Distinction

`docs/docs/setup/ai-setup.md` is the consumer setup playbook (for end users' repos). Repo development guidance is in root `AGENTS.md`.

## Commands

```bash
npm run docs:start
npm run docs:build
```
